John and everyone else,where are you all???You know I believe that suicide can be stopped,one thing about this issue is that when people think about suicide,most mention it to others,this is often very suttle and can go un-noticed,a window is opened that if we look and listen gives an oportunity to interviene.I have often thought about this and when I do I get out and look arround,it is often diffacult to see beyond one's own pain and this can leave a feeling that hope is not possible,stats mean absoutely nothing,charactor has no place,religon is to open and leaves too many escapes,the real issue is society,look at the current situation in our country,there is greater importance placed on the presidents sexual life,than the very real fact that due to the attention given this issue,people are going to die,now after the pictures are shown on TV ,they will then be seen as news worthy,this is what happens to those who are at risk of suicide.There are people who are almost empaths,they feel deeply and most have a very admirable set of values,they care very much for others and so much so that when they see as there is today,the devaluation of the human soul,hope cannot be seen on,in our world.These people care and society sees them as missfits.What I believe is that we as a society must place the truth before our leaders and the news media,these institutions have for too long enjoyed a total lack of responsibility,they are arrogent and express blatently a total disrespect for common decency,they protit from immorrality and profanity.They have done there best to put the internet out of the common persons reach,they will continue to do this and we must stop them.I put things out as I see them and I personally do not see this as a partison  issue,it's the truth fighting B.S.and pure lies.I hope we can get some feedback and keep the dialog going,I have read some very insitful issues here and will continue as I can,Later The Outlaw 11 Dan
